Well I'll put my 2 cents worth in here. If you have machines with Windows 
and 8 Megs RAM, Windows for Workgroups is the cheapest and most 
integrated method of networking. 

Lantastic is a terrific solution also. It is equally capable in home, or 
in small to medium business use.

The only pitfall with Lantastic if you use Windows is upcoming Chicago. 
If you use Windows for Workgroups, you will be able to upgrade to Chicago 
and keep going. If you network now with Lantastic, you will 1) have to 
wait for Lantastic to support Chicago, or 2) switch to Chicago's own 
networking (and waste the money you spent on Lantastic.) 

Either way you choose, I would suggest that you buy a reputable brand of 
Ethernet card, either WD or NE2000 compatible and use Lantastic AI 
(adapter independent) as opposed to buying a Lantastic hardware/software 
starter kit. You may regret it later if you switch to Chicago network and 
find the Lantastic proprietary cards lacking.

MD


